OL,3,CJersey's 'backdoor into the UK'
OL,4,Ccondemned by MPs
OL,6,FHowever, the island's Home Affairs
OL,7,FMinister, Deputy Mary le Hegarat,
OL,8,Fadmitted in the Assembly last week
OL,9,Fthat "it is quite clear with
OL,10,Fcorrespondence from the Home Office
OL,11,Fthat this is not a project they
OL,12,Fendorse."
OL,14,FShe added: "This heightens the risk
OL,15,Ffor us in relation to the Common
OL,16,FTravel Area and also potentially us
OL,17,Fbeing given a hard border."
