OL,3,CJersey's 'backdoor into the UK'
OL,4,Ccondemned by MPs
OL,6,FBut Deputy Ian Gorst, Jersey's
OL,7,FMinister for External Relations, says
OL,8,Fsuitable checks and balances are in
OL,9,Fplace to ensure the system isn't
OL,10,Fexploited as a pathway to the mainland.
OL,12,F"These arrivals on their ID card have
OL,13,Fto have a return ticket for the ferry
OL,14,Fand there have been no incidences of
OL,15,Fonward travel to other places within
OL,16,Fthe Common Travel Area.
OL,18,F"So we can be confident that our
OL,19,Fborder forces are protecting us and
OL,20,Fyet at the same time bringing this
OL,21,Fbenefit to Jersey's economy."
